Ok Rock, stylized as ONE OK ROCK (pronounced in Japanese as `one o`clock`), is a Japanese rock band formed in Tokyo, Japan in 2005. The band currently consists of Takahiro Moriuchi (vocals), Toru Yamashita (guitar/leader), Ryota Kohama (bass), and Tomoya Kanki (drums).The band`s name, ONE OK ROCK, comes from `one o`clock`, the time that the band used to practice on weekends. They chose to play at one o`clock in the morning because it was cheaper to use the rehearsal space during such hours. However, noticing that the Japanese language made no distinction between R`s and L`s, they changed `O`CLOCK` to `O`CROCK` (or `O`KROCK`), which was then separated to become `OK
